## Testing approach: MVP

This project uses **mvp** testing rigor — a smoke pyramid focused on critical paths and must-have requirements.

Write unit tests only where the logic is genuinely non-trivial (calculations, transformations, validations with business rules). For integration, test the happy path of each major data flow. For end-to-end, write exactly one test per distinct user journey; do not duplicate coverage already provided by lower-level tests.

Cover only functional requirements marked "must" in the PRD. Non-must requirements and edge cases are acknowledged but not tested unless they represent a known failure risk. Coverage is risk-weighted, not numeric — there is no line or branch coverage target for this project. If in doubt, write the test that catches the bug most likely to slip to production.

Skip visual regression, a11y matrix, and performance budget tests for this project. Those are tracked as future work when rigor is upgraded to `full`.
